                            java.lang.String p_continentValue)
        addContinent : Checks if the continent already exists or not. the new Continent would be added to a HashMap of the d_continents currently residing in the loaded map.
        Parameters:
        p_continentID - : unique ID for the new continent. Used for verifying if the continent is new.
        p_continentValue - : each continent has a value in is passed as String to the method but converted to Integer.
        Returns:
        true if the continent is new and added. false if the continent already exists.
        See Also:
        HashMap

      • addCountry

        public boolean addCountry(java.lang.String p_countryID,
                          java.lang.String p_continentID)
        addCountry: in a specific continent (continentID) a Country is added. First it would be validated to check if the continent and country already exist. in case the country is new, it would be added to the continent. The verification at this level remains solely on checking the validity of single objects not the whole map.
        Parameters:
        p_countryID - : the unique ID for each Country
        p_continentID - : the unique ID for each Continent
        Returns:
        : returns true if the new country is created. returns false if the country already exists.

      • addNeighbor

        public boolean addNeighbor(java.lang.String p_countryID,
                           java.lang.String p_neighborID)
        addNeighbor : first verifies if the country already exists then if neighbor is new. adds neighbor to a specific country. the neigbor and the country should be the same.
        Parameters:
        p_countryID - : unique ID for each country
        p_neighborID - : unique ID of the neighbor country
        Returns:
        false if country and neighbor are same. false if country or neighbor doesn't exists. false if the neighbor is already listed as neighbor to the country. true if the neighbor is new.

      • removeNeighbor

                              java.lang.String p_neighborID)

        Parameters:
        p_countryID - : unique ID for the country
        p_neighborID - : unique ID for the neighbor countries
        Returns:
        true on successful termination of removal process. false if the country or neigbor do not exits.

      • removeCountry

        public boolean removeCountry(java.lang.String p_countryID)

        Parameters:
        p_countryID - unique ID country
        Returns:
        true if the removing process terminates successfully.
